<h1>Conclusion</h1>
<p>Computer Worms are a relatively dated though still potentially harmful method of attacking computer networks. The implementation of basic computer safety protocols, education of cumputer users on methods to detect and avoid harmful data sources, and the use of antivirus software provides an effective wall to shield against these attacks.</p>

